# OYE STORIES — Walkthrough

## What Was Built

A complete **Telugu story book web app** called **"OYE STORIES"** by **Dasari Srikanth** — built with vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

### Files Modified

| File | Description |
|------|-------------|
| [index.html](file:///c:/Users/admin/OneDrive/Desktop/dust/storybook-app/index.html) | 5 views: Home, Reader, Admin Login, Dashboard, Add/Edit Form |
| [style.css](file:///c:/Users/admin/OneDrive/Desktop/dust/storybook-app/style.css) | Premium CSS with dark/light themes, glassmorphism, animations |
| [stories.js](file:///c:/Users/admin/OneDrive/Desktop/dust/storybook-app/stories.js) | 8 Telugu stories across 6 categories |
| [app.js](file:///c:/Users/admin/OneDrive/Desktop/dust/storybook-app/app.js) | Full app logic: routing, search, CRUD, likes, bookmarks |

---

## Features

### 👤 User Features
- View Telugu story cards in a responsive grid
- Search stories by title, author, or category
- Filter by category: పిల్లల, నీతి, భయానక, ప్రేమ, సాహస, హాస్య
- Read full stories with page-by-page navigation
- Adjust font size, like & bookmark stories
- Dark/Light mode toggle (persisted in localStorage)
- Keyboard navigation (arrow keys, Escape)

### 🔐 Admin Features
- Secure login (password: `oye@admin2024`)
- Dashboard with stats (total stories, categories, likes, bookmarks)
- Add new stories with full form
- Edit existing stories
- Delete stories with confirmation dialog
- Toast notifications for all actions

